ble means of gathering information about trends in employment and unemployment, and on pay. The countries of East-Central Europe and the former USSR have recognized their need of such statistiics and turned to the ILO to help them set up systems to provide data required by decision makers. This pioneering work shows how the old "command" economies are setting up brand new systems to classify occupations, to measure employment and unemployment, and to collect information on wages and labour costs, which will be useful to students of the area and essential for statisticians world-wide concerned with the challenge of instigating an entirely new statistical service.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2022) 0aLabor supplyzEurope, EasternvStatistics. 0aLabor supplyzFormer Soviet republicsvStatistics. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Labor.2bisacsh  aemployment, unemployment.1 aChernyshev, I., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDupre, M. T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEyraud, F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFoti, J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGorbacheva, T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGouriev, V., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHoffmann, E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHussmanns, R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKeleti, A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKiseleva, K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKux, J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLawrence, S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 